Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.79,0:00:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agreed to let you come\Nalong because, like Shea,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.00,0:00:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you yourself believed that coming\Nwith me was what's best for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.72,0:00:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You understood I had feelings for another,\Nbut still you wished to stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:23.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you should do what you\Nwanted to do. That's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now, you don't\Nappear that way anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.48,0:00:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, think about this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you come along? Should you stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.95,0:00:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it comes down to it,\NI'll take you back to Yaegashi myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.95,0:00:43.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.35,0:02:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quite a feat, building such\Na huge ship out of wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.71,0:02:51.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.12,0:02:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, keep it together.\NThis is going to be another terrible play.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.46,0:02:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.02,0:03:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this... A party?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.11,0:03:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, and not just with humans,\Nthere are demons and beastmen here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.20,0:03:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it seems rather extravagant...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.12,0:03:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.50,0:03:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all have prayed for peace and\Nrisked your lives in war to achieve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.51,0:03:43.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am truly happy to be able\Nto gather you all here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to end this war,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.68,0:03:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with a peace treaty no less,\Nin my generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.43,0:03:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A whole year has passed, and now\NI can witness this sight before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.52,0:03:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot help but feel moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.82,0:04:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this a celebration\Nfor the end of a war?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Given the context, that seems\Nto be the only explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.03,0:04:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe our assumption about the\Ntheme of Melusine's trial was wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.83,0:04:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know something\Nlike this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They must have worked tirelessly to\Nachieve peace. A great undertaking indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.00,0:04:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.46,0:04:21.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They couldn't have gotten\Nover every single grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.26,0:04:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But still, they're smiling\Ntogether like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has been one year since the peace\Ntreaty was signed, which makes me think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.27,0:04:34.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About how foolish this has been.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.02,0:04:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, truly foolish. Exchanging\Na toast with filthy animals,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.11,0:04:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,discussing the future with heathens...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.48,0:04:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was all the pinnacle of foolishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.07,0:04:47.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.49,0:04:50.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm talking about you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?!\NWhat's going on with--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.96,0:04:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.21,0:05:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.13,0:05:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said at the beginning,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.01,0:05:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm truly glad to see\Nthat you've all gathered here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.76,0:05:13.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Evil races, forsaken by our god,\Nclaiming to create a nation
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.14,0:05:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and pretending to be on equal footing with\Nus humans... Such a despicable situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.15,0:05:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fools who have turned their backs against\NEhit, the one and only god and creator,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.44,0:05:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to worship some worthless pagan god,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.86,0:05:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no longer need to be tolerated,\Nstarting today!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.03,0:05:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no peace\Nwithout total annihilation!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.96,0:05:42.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'm truly glad
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:48.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could wipe out the authorities\Nof every nation today!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, true believers!\NUnleash the judgment of our god!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.10,0:06:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Ehit, my lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.11,0:06:05.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you watching?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.99,0:06:09.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.04,0:06:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.08,0:06:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.71,0:06:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.80,0:06:30.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine. That was hard to watch...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.84,0:06:35.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But anyway, is that it, though?\NWe didn't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess the idea is, to move forward,\Nwe should go into the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.98,0:06:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the point of that last vision\Nwas to just show us what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.44,0:06:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show what kind of madness that god can\Ncreate, and then make us search the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.24,0:06:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite a nasty setup,\Nespecially for locals from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.66,0:07:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would make them unable\Nto believe in their own god.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.46,0:07:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That last vision...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.30,0:07:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though the war ended,\Nthat person betrayed everyone, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.26,0:07:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.80,0:07:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But didn't it seem a little strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.56,0:07:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When he came up to that stage, everyone\Nlooked up at him with respect and love.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.65,0:07:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he had been hiding such a\Ndeep hatred of beastmen and demons,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.78,0:07:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would he have been able\Nto gather that much respect?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.70,0:07:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The way he spoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it seems more natural to think that\Nsomething happened to make him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.66,0:07:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,suddenly change during\Nthe one year after the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.41,0:07:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's god-related, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.90,0:08:08.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,String?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.86,0:08:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now there's a physical trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.32,0:08:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These Liberators are all quite awful...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.66,0:08:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.71,0:08:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.13,0:08:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.47,0:08:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a damn bother!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.82,0:08:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.20,0:08:59.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.91,0:09:02.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here, Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.46,0:09:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.83,0:09:10.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.50,0:09:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.26,0:09:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, could you please console me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.27,0:09:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.02,0:09:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.48,0:09:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Killing an enemy, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.65,0:09:31.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like you just tried to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.29,0:09:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}, why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.17,0:10:00.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking in Kaori's voice.\NStop moving in Kaori's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.80,0:10:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see through you, the piece\Nof trash infesting in Kaori's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.56,0:10:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might understand, but there's\Nnothing you can do. This woman is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.82,0:10:22.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.87,0:10:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This woman is yours!\NAre you going to hurt her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.12,0:10:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic ammunition won't hurt Kaori's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.13,0:10:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll only cause pain to you,\Nthe thing haunting her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.30,0:10:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you destroy me, it'll break her, too!\NIs that what you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.26,0:10:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, good--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.60,0:10:53.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you insane?!\NDon't you care about this woman?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.36,0:10:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I stopped attacking, you're\Nnot going to give Kaori her body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.03,0:11:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you said it yourself. If I don't\Ndestroy you, Kaori's soul is fine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.45,0:11:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then all I have to do is make\Nyou want to leave her body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.58,0:11:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just torture you while\Nbeing careful not to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.83,0:11:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.79,0:11:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You threatened someone important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't think you can\Njust vanish painlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.46,0:11:20.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do everything in\Nmy power to keep you alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.05,0:11:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will feel every form of pain.\NBut I won't let you go insane either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're my enemy, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.27,0:11:31.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't ever kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.67,0:11:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I'll send you off properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.77,0:12:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That thing seems\Nto have left completely...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.75,0:12:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.71,0:12:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Giving my answer, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.17,0:12:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.58,0:12:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, to the question\Nof why I came along
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.05,0:12:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and whether I want to stay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.47,0:12:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you, Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}. Truly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.43,0:12:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I want to stay with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.31,0:12:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Won't you just be tormented, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.44,0:12:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not like Shea.\NYou don't want Yue to be part of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.94,0:13:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I do want to\Nhave you all for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.07,0:13:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be your only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.20,0:13:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will be jealous and\Nwill feel inferior to Yue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.29,0:13:12.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll feel painful for me at times.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.71,0:13:16.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.46,0:13:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I know for sure that\NI'll regret backing off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.01,0:13:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know for sure that the best thing\Nfor me is to stay by your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.72,0:13:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you want, Kaori,\Nthen I have nothing more to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.48,0:13:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.49,0:13:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}, can you repeat\Nthat thing you said earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.87,0:13:50.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.99,0:13:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did they threaten\Nthat made you so angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.87,0:13:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm. I don't know\Nwhat you're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:14:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Just say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.26,0:14:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.18,0:14:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a magic circle? Did we reach\Nend of the dungeon already?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.98,0:14:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I just didn't\Nexpect it to end so soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.19,0:14:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If feels a bit too easy,\Ncompared to the other labyrinths.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.78,0:14:30.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, for the people\Nwho grew up in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.24,0:14:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who have strong faiths,\Nif they were shown that madness...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.92,0:14:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be enough to break them, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.30,0:14:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good timing.\NHey, everything all right on your side?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.14,0:14:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.85,0:14:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.43,0:14:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori-{\i1}san{\i0}, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.73,0:15:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you injured?\NWhat about your healing magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.81,0:15:06.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine, thank you for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually mostly just being spoiled.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.99,0:15:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Kaori, can you walk now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.70,0:15:15.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I was able to the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.37,0:15:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.91,0:15:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what happened? Hmm? Speak up, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.79,0:15:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you do the lovey-dovey\Nwith Kaori? Lovey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.59,0:15:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, haven't felt that in a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.30,0:15:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.55,0:15:36.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just shared a little kiss\Nwith Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.31,0:15:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?! Who started it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.93,0:15:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.81,0:15:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun {\i0}got angry for me, so\NI couldn't hold back, and I went for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.69,0:15:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, just like me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.86,0:15:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.45,0:15:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you'd turn tail and run.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.37,0:16:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Hajime-{\i1}kun {\i0}recommended\Nthat I do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.83,0:16:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the differences between Yue and I\Nare kind of old news anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.17,0:16:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're taking a "so what" attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.88,0:16:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.63,0:16:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, me coming here\Nwas already an act of defiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.38,0:16:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the gap between us became apparent,\NI just forgot about that for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.43,0:16:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I definitely showed him\Na miserable side of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.77,0:16:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have just given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.19,0:16:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you threatened by me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.40,0:16:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get carried away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.73,0:16:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I'm someone important\Nto Hajime-{\i1}kun {\i0}now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.20,0:16:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'm going to try\Nto become someone special.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.24,0:16:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what anyone says.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.00,0:16:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. In that case, I will accept\Nyour challenge, just as before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.17,0:16:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.47,0:17:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found it. The power of restoration.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.87,0:17:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't cling to that god.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.95,0:17:25.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make your own decisions,\Nmove forward on your own feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.79,0:17:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Happiness only comes\Nto those with a free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.47,0:17:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The proof of conquest...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.76,0:17:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we have four of them. We can take\Non the labyrinth at the Sea of Trees!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.15,0:17:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Forced ejection?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:17:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yue, spatial magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.66,0:18:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.64,0:18:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only is it unkillable, it melts\Nanything and can even control the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.77,0:18:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are we supposed to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.81,0:18:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now what? Last time,\Nwe attacked it with fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.90,0:18:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.57,0:18:45.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can assume we can't\Nuse Yue and Tio's fire magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.75,0:18:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime, any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.67,0:18:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one way\Nto use fire while underwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.21,0:18:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll vaporize that jelly faster\Nthan it can regenerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.72,0:18:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it works, we should\Nbe able to take it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.84,0:19:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.59,0:19:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I need time.\NI just need three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.30,0:19:05.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can just hold\Non for three minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.39,0:19:11.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's trying to swallow us whole!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.19,0:19:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it comes down to it,\NI'll transform to protect everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.23,0:19:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, I need more time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.24,0:19:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hajime, my boy.\NLemme give you a hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.79,0:19:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leh-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.62,0:19:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right,\Nit's Leh-{\i1}san{\i0}, your old buddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.29,0:19:38.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? You can take out the\NDevourer if you have three minutes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.17,0:19:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand, but thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.89,0:19:43.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey there, Shea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.80,0:19:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leh-{\i1}san{\i0}? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.85,0:19:52.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was just hanging around when\NI noticed a huge and familiar magic power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.81,0:19:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After sensing trouble, I rushed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.90,0:19:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those fish... And the "Devourer"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.78,0:20:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guided those fish using my powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.32,0:20:03.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.45,0:20:07.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Devourer is an ancient monster\Nthat lives in the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.79,0:20:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a natural disaster of sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.83,0:20:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some say it's the ancestor of monsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.08,0:20:14.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's done!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.97,0:20:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat up and die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.39,0:20:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Warn me before making explosions!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.27,0:20:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Leh-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.32,0:20:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been three days since Ai-{\i1}chan{\i0}\Nwent to the Divine Mountain...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.49,0:20:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ishtar-{\i1}san {\i0}said she'd be back very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.82,0:20:47.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lily won't come back either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.95,0:20:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The king said there's\Nnothing to worry about, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.29,0:20:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which,\NNia-{\i1}san {\i0}is gone too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.37,0:20:55.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:20:58.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's concerning when these things\Nhappen all at once like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.29,0:21:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let's go ask\Nthe guards what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.55,0:21:06.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought so too,\Nbut I couldn't find them anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.30,0:21:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.22,0:21:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meld-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about Ai-{\i1}chan{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.64,0:21:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard Aiko went to the Divine Mountain\Nto discuss the issue of Hajime Nagumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.02,0:21:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She went and hasn't come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.07,0:21:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hasn't come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.53,0:21:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All her guards are gone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.57,0:21:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Several others have suddenly gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.45,0:21:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.00,0:21:35.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we're doing\Nour own investigation, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.51,0:21:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My lord feels that what you are\Ntrying to do is an inconvenience.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.80,0:21:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He believes that what your student\Nis trying to do is far more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.23,0:21:57.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, until the right time comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.56,0:22:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you will temporarily leave\Nmy lord's game board.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.95,0:23:38.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode, "A New Vow."